Node "Ferd_5_7b_01"
notes "The Ferd_5_7b_* path is where the PC can get Ferdinand blind drunk and trick him into joining her as a follower PC. If it backfires, though, the PC ends up drunk and loses the chance to form a relationship with Ferdinand. She must then complete the bones quest if she is going to convince Ferdinand to become an NPC follower.\nThis path is accessable on both the first and second dates, although the get-out option will take the player back to the correct dialogue depending on how many dates she has been on."
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "[Ferdinand raises an eyebrow in surprise.] Are you sure? This stuff Sara sell, it take the paint off the wall!"
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Absolutely sure. Are you afraid a woman could drink you under the table, Ferdinand?" linkto "Ferd_5_7b_02"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I'll have some water instead, in that case." linkto "Ferd_5_7a_1"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I'll have a Nuka Cola instead, in that case." linkto "Ferd_5_7a_1"  notes "Add a bottle of Nuka Cola to the PC's inventory."
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I'll have a beer instead, in that case." linkto "Ferd_5_7a_1"  notes "Add a bottle of beer to the PC's inventory."
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I'm sorry, this isn't going to work. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes "Make the variable Ferd_Date_Blown=1. This means Ferdinand will not go on any more dates with the female PC and she can only convince him to join her as an NPC follower if she completes the bones quest.\nFerdinand will not talk to the PC again and will immediately walk back to his normal spot in the Wasteland Explorers' tent. Only then will he talk to the PC."
              }
}
